# Physics Simulation Website

A full-stack web app that transforms boring theory into engaging, hands-on learning by visualizing **three** physics phenomena:

- **Pendulum motion**
- **Magnetic fields**
- **Planetary motion with gravitational fields**

## Tech Stack

**Frontend**
- React (Vite)
- Three.js (WebGL)
- React Three Fiber / react-three-rapier (physics)
- Tailwind CSS
- (Some UI built with Bootstrap where useful)

**Backend**
- Node.js + Express
- MySQL (via mysql2)  
- REST API

**Infra / Dev**
- Docker & Docker Compose
- Canvas API + WebGL rendering
- Hot reload in dev
- GitHub Codespaces (`.devcontainer` included)

---

## Quick Start (Docker)

```bash
# 1) clone
git clone https://github.com/Rameen222/Physics-Simulation-Website-.git
cd Physics-Simulation-Website-

# 2) create envs from templates (never commit real .env files)
cp backend/.env.example backend/.env
cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env

# 3) run
docker compose up --build



NOTE: could alternatively also run the code in Github codepsace or directly on local dev
